                    "EN": "In order for me to be motivated to make an effort, I have to be interested and see a purpose in doing what is being asked of me.\u00a0PROP:For the student to be motivated to make a concrete effort, he/she must be interested in the subject and see a concrete purpose in what he/she is being asked to do.",
                    "FR": "Pour que l\u2019\u00e9l\u00e8ve/l\u2019\u00e9tudiant soit motiv\u00e9 \u00e0 faire un effort concret, il/elle doit \u00eatre int\u00e9ress\u00e9(e) par le sujet et voir un but concret dans ce qu\u2019on lui demande."
