                    "EN": "Sometimes the student sets his/her goals too high - he/she can't reach them and feels bad. Sometimes he/she sets goals too low - he/she achieves them easily, but still does not feel at his/her best because the goals achieved are experienced as failures in relation to his/her abilities.",
