                            "PL": "Ucze\u0144/Uczennica powinien/powinna przeanalizowa\u0107 swoje dotychczasowe sukcesy i pora\u017cki. Jakie strategie uczenia si\u0119 sprawiaj\u0105 mu/jej najwi\u0119ksz\u0105 satysfakcj\u0119? Ile  wymagaj\u0105 od niego/niej czasu? Na podstawie tych pyta\u0144 ucze\u0144/uczennica powinien/powinna zaplanowa\u0107 swoj\u0105 przysz\u0142\u0105 strategi\u0119 nauki.",
                            "EN": "'The student should be helped to examine his/her approach to his/her work. Reflexively he/she should ask himself/herself what he/she could improve based on past assignments, exams and exercises. He/she should refine his/her thinking by focusing on how he/she learns and studies. He/she should then devise a plan to organize him/herself for future assignments and/or exams and keep in mind the imperative of meeting deadlines according to his/her learning style.",
                            "FR": "\u00ab L\u2019\u00e9tudiant(e) doit \u00eatre aider \u00e0 examiner sa fa\u00e7on d'aborder son travail. De mani\u00e8re r\u00e9flexive il/elle doit se demander ce qu\u2019il/elle pourrait am\u00e9liorer en se basant sur ses devoirs, examens et exercices pass\u00e9s. Il/elle doit parfaire sa r\u00e9flexion en se focalisant sur sa fa\u00e7on d'apprendre et d'\u00e9tudier. Il/elle doit ensuite concevoir un plan afin de s'organiser pour ses futurs devoirs et/ou examens et garder \u00e0 l\u2019esprit le respect imp\u00e9ratif des d\u00e9lais en fonction de son style d'apprentissage."
