            "EN": "A communicative child is one who has the confidence to give something to others, but also to learn something from them. He or she has the opportunity to gain information and actively seeks it out. He or she asks questions so that he or she can be sure of his or her thoughts, doubts. He shares opinions, prepares arguments, thereby learning on the fly and remembering. Gives himself/herself a chance for better relations.",
